ppo_ctrl_`); webhook metrics in `metrics/webhook.go` (prefix `mto_ppo_wh_`); shared metrics in `metrics/common_metrics.go`.\n2. Declare a package-level `prometheus.Counter` / `prometheus.Histogram` variable.\n3. Initialize and register it inside the corresponding `init*Metrics()` function using `metrics2.Registry.MustRegister(...)`.\n4. Increment/observe the metric at the call site.\n\n### Write a unit test for the webhook\n\n1. Use Ginkgo `Describe`/`Context`/`It` blocks (never `t.Run`).\n2. Construct test pods with the fluent builder: `builder.NewPod().WithName(\"test\").WithNamespace(\"default\").WithContainersImages(\"quay.io/example/app:latest\").Build()`.\n3. Override `imageInspectionCache` (package-level `image.ICache` in `pod_model.go`) with a test double to avoid real registry calls.\n4. Run focused tests with: `GINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='your test name'\" make unit`.\n\n### Add a new execution mode\n\n1. Add a `bool` flag variable and bind it in `bindFlags()` in `cmd/main.go`.\n2. Add the mode to `validateFlags()` — exactly one mode must be set.\n3. Construct a unique leader election ID by prefixing the base ID `208d7abd.multiarch.openshift.io`.\n4. Implement a `RunMyMode(mgr ctrl.Manager)` function and call it from `main()`.\n5. If the mode needs ClusterPodPlacementConfig access, set `enableCPPCInformer = true` and start the syncer.\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n| Symptom | Where to look |\n|---|---|\n| Pods stuck in `SchedulingGated` state | Check pod placement controller logs (`--enable-ppc-controllers`); check `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` counter; verify pull secrets are accessible; check `MaxRetryCount` (5) not exhausted |\n| Webhook not adding scheduling gate | Confirm `MutatingWebhookConfiguration` is present; check CPPC `namespaceSelector` — namespace may be excluded; verify pod is not in `kube-*` or operator namespace; check if pod is owned by DaemonSet |\n| High image inspection latency | Cache may be cold after a global pull secret rotation (cache is cleared on `StoreGlobalPullSecret`); check `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_image_seconds` histogram; verify registry reachability |\n| CPPC status shows Degraded | Check controller and webhook deployment rollout status; `PodPlacementControllerNotRolledOut` or `PodPlacementWebhookNotRolledOut` conditions will indicate which component is not ready |\n| openshift-* pods getting gated unexpectedly | `openshift-*` namespaces are NOT hardcoded exclusions — configure `namespaceSelector` on ClusterPodPlacementConfig with `multiarch.openshift.io/exclude-pod-placement DoesNotExist` |\n\n## Agentic Documentation\n\n| Document | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| [agentic/DESIGN.md](agentic/DESIGN.md) | Architecture: pipeline, execution modes, singleton patterns, namespace exclusions |\n| [agentic/DEVELOPMENT.md](agentic/DEVELOPMENT.md) | Step-by-step guides for adding fields, modes, and running code generation |\n| [agentic/TESTING.md](agentic/TESTING.md) | Test pyramid, Ginkgo patterns, builder API, mocking image inspection |\n| [agentic/RELIABILITY.md](agentic/RELIABILITY.md) | SLO targets, metric catalog, PromQL examples, alerting thresholds |\n| [agentic/SECURITY.md](agentic/SECURITY.md) | Namespace exclusions as security controls, RBAC, webhook validation boundaries |\n\n### Component deep-dives\n\n- [Pod placement webhook](agentic/design-docs/components/pod-placement-webhook.md)\n- [PPO controller](agentic/design-docs/components/ppo-controller.md)\n- [Image inspection cache](agentic/design-docs/components/image-inspection-cache.md)\n\n### Concepts\n\n- [Execution modes](agentic/domain/concepts/execution-modes.md)","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
